curam.util.events.struct

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.type.struct.Struct<Event>
      • curam.util.events.struct.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DeepCloneable, java.io.Serializable

    public final class Event
extends Struct<Event>
    Represents an event in Curam. This allows Curam application code to send notifications about certain actions having being performed to other application code. Interested components can register a handler that will be invoked when the event is raised. Events are raised via the raiseEvent API call.

    • Field Detail

      • primaryEventData

        public long primaryEventData
        A unique identifier related to the event class from which the event is raised. The identifier is passed to the event handler which uses it to find additional information relevant to handling the event. For example, where the business object type specified for an event is equal to 'Case', the event data could be case identifier, i.e. primaryEventData='12345'.

        EVENT_DATA -> long

      • secondaryEventData

        public long secondaryEventData
        The event output mapping data is optional. It is intended for events that must represent an association between two entities. An example of this would be an event class of RELATIONSHIP with an associated event type of CHANGED. In this case the primary and secondary event data would represent the relationship that has changed between the two entities.

        EVENT_DATA -> long

      • raisedByUser

        public java.lang.String raisedByUser
        The name of the user that raised the event.

        EVENT_RAISED_BY_USER -> String
